data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async, but in EF Core 11 that opt-in is gone — all synchronous calls (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) **always throw** at runtime. There is no workaround; you must go async.

Here's the fix for your repository:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
1. Every method becomes `async Task<T>` (or `async Task`)
2. `ToList()` → `await ToListAsync()`, `First()` → `await FirstAsync()`, `Count()` → `await CountAsync()`, `SaveChanges()` → `await SaveChangesAsync()`
3. Rename methods to the `*Async` convention
4. All callers up the chain must also be updated to `await` these methods

Remove any `.EnableSyncOverAsync()` or equivalent opt-in from your `DbContext` configuration — it no longer has any effect.
